cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM 

This paper deals with the problem of zero-shot learning using generative adversarial networks (GANs) and proposes a new method to alleviate the issue of feature confusion. The paper focuses on computer vision tasks and proposes a new metric to quantify feature confusion. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves machine learning techniques and proposes a new loss function, so it is also likely to belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a new metric and involves natural language processing tasks, so it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper involves image and video processing tasks, so it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
